  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0b9f\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bc7\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd - \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbe\u0b9e\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0ba9 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9c\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bc7\u0b95\u0bb0",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Don't go to petrol stations and ask for tokens - Minister Kanchana Wijesekara",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Only those waiting in queues were advised to register and issue tokens on the day when the fuel tanker was announced not to reach the country on the specified day. Therefore, Power Minister Kanchana Wijesekara has asked the general public not to go to the fuel stations to claim tickets or wait for them.",
        "He said this at a press conference held at the Ministry of Power on Sunday.",
        "After it was confirmed that the ship scheduled to arrive in the country on 23rd June will not arrive, we have advised people not to wait in queues unnecessarily. Also, the security department was advised to register and issue tokens only to those who had been waiting in queues for a few days prior to that.",
        "This step was taken to send people in queues from there and to avoid long queues. But it has gone into the wrong system and completed issuing tickets to those already waiting in the queues and steps have been taken to issue them to the new joiners as well. This is not the advice we have given.",
        "Thus we request you not to gather together to get tickets. After the fuel is imported, steps are taken to distribute it under a proper mechanism. Until then, don't go to gas stations and claim coupons. That is not the system. On the day when the fuel tanker was declared non-arrival, only those waiting in queues were advised to issue tickets.",
        "Now it is unfortunately being run as a different business. 1000 - 2000 fuel is sold in the black markets today. They sell stored fuel. Some people use it. He said that despite the fact that fuel was not dispensed to any of the petroleum corporation-owned filling stations, vehicle consumption did not decrease significantly."
      ],
